  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study aims to describe the postoperative functions of patients with ischaemic lower
      extremities after undergoing revascularisation surgery . Primary endpoints will focus on
      complications in the post-anaesthesia care unit (PACU) which prevent discharge from PACU to
      the general ward. This include Aldrete scores and other complications that can be registrered
      descriptively. Furthermore, the study seeks to compare the complications outcomes between
      acute and elective revascularisation surgery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
